deck: A waitress in love with Dead Duck, she fell for him after he came to collect the soul of her sister Paper Goodly.
description:
Origins

Cotton Goodly first appears in the Dead Duck storyline A minion of Death takes a holiday. She grabs Dead Duck and kisses him passionately. She fell in love with him after her sister Paper Goodly died thanks to a faulty electric toothbrush.
name: Cotton Goodly

deck: Dean is a History Cleaner for J.P. Yorick, he handles major historical events when they go awry.
description:
Origins

Dean first appears in the Dead Duck storyline Four Score, relating to the botched assassination of Abraham Lincoln. Dean is called in when others fail to make sure major historical events remain as they are.

Abilities.

Dean possesses no head but seems to understand speech and have someway of sensing other beings. He also carries a small briefcase with a multitude of weaponry including a machete and a machine gun.
name: Dean

deck: Dracula is a nemesis to Dead Duck, his first real enemy when they met at summer camp.
description:
Origins

Dracula first appears in the Dead Duck storyline Summer Time Bruise, he is the first enemy of Dead Duck and constantly pulls evil pranks on Dead Duck that cause him physical harm.

Abilities

Dracula has green scaly skin, fangs, the ability to turn others into his undead slaves.

Weaknesses

Dracula is weak against sunlight, garlic and a stake through the heart.
name: Dracula

deck: Dead Duck's first crush, Gwen the witch.
description:
Origins

Gwen first appears in the Dead Duck storyline Summer Time Bruise, she immediately falls for Dead Duck and his first crush, unfortunately she is turned into a cookie and eaten soon after.

Abilities

Gwen is a witch and has magical powers through the use of her wand, only one power was shown, the power of transformation.
name: Gwen

deck: Zeebub, the devil himself, he wore a costume around everyone except Dead Duck who learned the truth of his identity.
description:
Origins

Zeebub first appears in the Dead Duck storyline Summer Time Bruise as the head camp counselor for Dead Duck and his group of evil campers, Dickie Nixon, Adolf Hitler and Dracula.

Abilities

Zeebub displays a few abilities but his character does have limited amounts of time in the storyline, so not all abilities were shown.
name: Zeebub

deck: Zachary Johnson was the owner and CEO of Z.J. Toys and secretly the Jack-in-the-Box, an identity he inherited from his father.
description:
Origin

Zachary's father, Jack Johnson, was one of the first African Americans to work in the toy manufacturing industry and design toys for the Whamco Corporation in the 1960s. He was the first Jack-in-the-Box from 1964 to his death in 1983.

His son, Zachary Johnson, owner and CEO of Z.J. Toys, took the identity of Jack-in-the-Box from 1989 until recently.

Due to his wife pregnancy and visitations from three alternate future versions of his to-be-born child, showing him what his son might become if his father kept fighting crime and ultimately die, he left the role to his protege, Roscoe James, active from now on.
